===Etymology===
From {{etyl|it|en}} {{term|lang=it|dilettante}}, prop. present participle of {{term|dilettare||to delight}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{term|delectare||to delight|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|UK}} {{IPA|/dɪləˈtɒnti/|lang=en}}
* {{a|US}} {{IPA|/ˈdɪlɪˌtɑnt/|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|dilettanti|dilettantes}}

# An [[amateur]], someone who [[dabble]]s in a field out of casual interest rather than as a profession or serious interest.
# {{context|sometimes|offensive|lang=en}} A person with a general but [[superficial]] interest in any art or a branch of [[knowledge]].

